    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Preventing Consonant-Heavy Racks</h2>

    <p>The best strategy is prevention. Good rack leave — the tiles you keep after each play — dramatically reduces your chance of drawing a consonant-heavy rack next turn.</p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900/20 border border-green-200 dark:border-green-700 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 mb-2">✓ Good Leave</p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-green-600 dark:text-green-200 space-y-1 list-disc pl-4">
          <li>Keep 1-2 vowels in your leave</li>
          <li>Retain high-flex consonants (S, R, T, N)</li>
          <li>Dump duplicates and low-flex tiles (V, W, C)</li>
          <li>Preserve bingo-friendly combos (ING, TION)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/20 border border-red-200 dark:border-red-700 rounded-lg p-4">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-red-700 dark:text-red-300 mb-2">✗ Bad Leave</p>
        <ul class="text-sm text-red-600 dark:text-red-200 space-y-1 list-disc pl-4">
          <li>Keeping all consonants to "save" a vowel-heavy play</li>
          <li>Holding duplicate consonants (BB, CC, DD)</li>
          <li>Retaining Q, X, Z without supporting vowels</li>
          <li>Playing only your vowels and keeping 4+ consonants</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

